Smart charge your car with ev.energy: a greener, smarter way to charge your electric vehicle. We're compatible with Tesla or any electric vehicle using a Rolec HomeSmart EV charger!

A SMARTER WAY TO CHARGE
We manage charging on your electric car, shifting you away from peak times by automatically charging overnight using the greenest, cheapest energy available.

SET IT AND FORGET IT
Plug in your EV at home and use our app to set when you need your car ready by. We'll communicate with your car or charger and take care of the rest.

SAVE MONEY, CHARGE GREENER
Saving is easy - we'll smart charge your vehicle at the times best for your energy bill, the environment and the grid.

TRACK YOUR USAGE
Easily track your EV’s carbon impact and energy consumption at home and on the go (On the go tracking currently only available for Tesla drivers who sign in with their Tesla account).

READY WHEN YOU NEED IT
Need your car to charge right away? Override our smart charging schedule at any time by tapping the Boost button.

---

**How does it work?**

Smart charging works by scheduling the time at which your EV charges based on your energy tariff and the current carbon intensity of the grid.

**Can I Smart Charge with any EV on any charger?**

Smart charging is available at your home address. If you drive a Tesla, you can Smart Charge on any home charger in the UK and Ireland by signing in with their Tesla Account. Alternatively, you can Smart Charge ANY electric vehicle if you've installed a Rolec HomeSmart EV charger at home.

**What's in it for me?**

Smart Charging with ev.energy maximises the amount of renewable energy you use overnight and minimises the cost to you - all while ensuring your vehicle is ready to go when you need it.

** Feedback **

If you're using the ev.energy app, we’d would like to know what you think. Is there something we can improve? Please let us know via support@ev.energy.

Need help? Find helpful information in our support articles - http://support.ev.energy

For further information, visit us at http://ev.energy
